               <p>CATHERINE ODAM. I am the <rs id="t18320906-461-viclabel2600" type="occupation">wife</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320906-461-victim3692 t18320906-461-viclabel2600"></join> of Moses Odam - we live in Cleveland-street, Fitzroy-square; he is a <rs id="t18320906-461-viclabel2601" type="occupation">cabinetmaker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320906-461-victim3690 t18320906-461-viclabel2601"></join>. On the 11th of September I was standing at <placeName id="t18320906-461-crimeloc2602">Westminster-bridge</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18320906-461-crimeloc2602" type="placeName" value="Westminster-bridge"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18320906-461-crimeloc2602" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320906-461-off2598 t18320906-461-crimeloc2602"></join>, when there was a crowd looking at a rowing-match; the prisoners came up to me, and shortly afterwards I saw Bonner draw his hand from my right side pocket - I then heard him call to the other prisoner, who was just behind him; I saw him put the money into Jones' hand, and they walked on; I missed 4s. 6d. and 5d. in halfpence - my husband was near me; I told him - he followed the prisoners - I looked for a constable, and gave them in charge; they were walking at the other end of the bridge.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18320906-461-person3693">
                  ROBERT 
                  GLASGOW
               <interp inst="t18320906-461-person3693" type="surname" value="GLASGOW"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320906-461-person3693" type="given" value="ROBERT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320906-461-person3693" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             (Police-constable P 21). I took the prisoners: I found on Jones one half-crown, one shilling, and 4 1/2d., and on Bonner one half-crown, and 3 1/4d.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18320906-461-person3694">
                  CATHERINE 
                  ODAM
               <interp inst="t18320906-461-person3694" type="surname" value="ODAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320906-461-person3694" type="given" value="CATHERINE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320906-461-person3694" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . The prisoners were taken from five to ten minutes afterwards - I had no half-crowns; my money was in shillings and sixpences.</p>
               <p>Jones' Defence. I was going to see the rowing-match; Bonner touched me, and asked me to go over the bridge- he said he was going to a boat.</p>
               <p>Bonner's Defence. I saw Jones, and went with him to try to borrow a boat, to follow the rowing-match; I was cutting an apple, and the officer took us.</p>
               <p>MOSES ODAM. My wife told me what had happened, and that the prisoners had her money - I watched them, and told her to get an officer; they walked along the bridge, and got a little past the middle - a third person joined them, and after a conversation of a minute or two, he left them, and they set down - I watched till my wife brought the officer.</p>
               <p>JONES - <rs id="t18320906-461-verdict2603" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18320906-461-verdict2603" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 18.</p>
